{
  "stem": "12494.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the small button was the soccer ball, and the big buttons were the players of soccer.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you could do that on the window sill in school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, in-- in the intermission.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was substantial [INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was actually a fairly complicated thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My dad and I always wanted me to go to the university, which was very difficult in Hungary because of what started out in the 1920s as a so-called numerus clausus, a limited number of Jews, [INAUDIBLE], a limited number of Jews at the institutes of higher education.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then gradually, turned into what was referred to, casually, as a numerus [NON-ENGLISH] that the number became close to zero.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Starting 1938, '39, it was almost impossible to get to the universities if you were a Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But people with influence could manage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so my [? dad and I ?] in 1943, when I would graduate from high school, I would-- I would go to university.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the protector of-- the protector of my university education, a gentleman named Bela Kenez, who was a former Minister of the Interior of Hungary, talked to my father about a year before my graduation from the gymnasium and said, if you really want me to get Arthur into the university, he better become a public student, rather than a private student as I was in the past.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because as a private student, even I couldn't help him get in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was on the Board of Directors of several of my father's enterprises.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so my father reluctantly decided that I should go to the gymnasium of the-- I should become a public student at the gymnasium of the best Jewish community, which was different from the Budapest Orthodox Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
